on the author's experience in the making and implementation of U.S. policy in the Obama administration, this book examines that real world experience and finds important lessons for the disarmament enterprise. Central conclusions of the work are that other nuclear-armed states are not prepared to join the United States in making reductions, and that unilateral steps by the United States to disarm further would be harmful to its interests and those of its allies. The book ultimately argues in favor of patience and persistence in the implementation of a balanced approach to nuclear strategy that encompasses political efforts to reduce nuclear dangers along with military efforts to deter them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aDeterrence (Strategy). 0aDiplomatic relations. 0aMilitary policy. 0aNational securityxUnited States. 0aNational securityzUnited States. 0aNational security. 0aNuclear weaponsxGovernment policyxUnited States. 0aNuclear weaponsxGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aNuclear weaponsxGovernment policy. 4aNuclear Posture Review. 4aarms control. 4aassurance. 4adeterrence. 4aextended deterrence. 4anonproliferation. 4anuclear strategy. 4astrategic stability. 70(DE-588)4000230-50(DE-627)1064017850(DE-576)208837353aAbschreckung2gnd. 70(DE-588)4003431-80(DE-627)1063896020(DE-576)208851569aAtomstrategie2gnd. 70(DE-588)4003434-30(DE-627)1063895990(DE-576)208851577aKernwaffe2gnd. 70(DE-588)4057952-90(DE-627)1061490750(DE-576)209124202aStrategie2gnd. 70(DE-588)4204973-80(DE-627)1051392540(DE-576)210165766aKonzeption2gnd. 70(DE-588)7791249-40(DE-627)6773929660(DE-576)357734777aNukleare Abschreckung2gnd. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Security (National & International).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2